AIM
To create class with and without object

Algorithm: Class with Object
Step 1:Start
Step 2:Define a class Student
Step 3:Assign values to variables: name, age, address
Step 4:Create an object of the class
Step 5:Access and print the values using the object
Step 6:Stop

Code: Class with Object
class Student:
    name = "Tanya"
    age = "20"
    address = "Bangalore"

details = Student()

print("Name is", details.name)
print("Age is", details.age)
print("Address is", details.address)

Output: Class with Object
Name is Tanya
Age is 20
Address is Bangalore



ALGORITHM: CLASS WITHOUT OBJECT 
Step 1:Start
Step 2:Define a class Student
Step 3:Take input for name and USN
Step 4:Take input for 5 subject marks
Step 5:Define a method total_marks()
Step 6:Calculate total marks by adding all marks
Step 7:Print total marks, name, and USN
Step 8:Create object of class
Step 9:Call the method using object
Step 10:Stop

CODE: CLASS WITHOUT OBJECT 
class Student:
    name = input("Enter the name: ")
    usn = input("Enter the usn: ")
    marks1 = int(input("Enter the marks1: "))
    marks2 = int(input("Enter the marks2: "))
    marks3 = int(input("Enter the marks3: "))
    marks4 = int(input("Enter the marks4: "))
    marks5 = int(input("Enter the marks5: "))

    def total_marks(self):
        total = (self.marks1 + self.marks2 + self.marks3 +
                 self.marks4 + self.marks5)
        print("Total Marks:", total)
        print("Name:", self.name)
        print("USN:", self.usn)


obj = Student()
obj.total_marks()

OUTPUT: CLASS WITHOUT OBJECT 
Enter the name: Tanya
Enter the usn: 24BCAR0520
Enter the marks1: 80
Enter the marks2: 91
Enter the marks3: 88
Enter the marks4: 75
Enter the marks5: 94
Total Marks: 428
Name: Tanya
USN: 24BCAR0520

